64 Degrees.description: 64 Degrees specializes in burgers, stir-fry, and tacos and is located near Mandeville center and York Hall. It derives its name from 1) the average temperature of La Jolla, 2) the year Revelle College was founded (1964), and 3) the height of the college’s namesake, Roger Revelle (6’4”).
64 Degrees.subtitle: burgerrsssssss
64 Degrees.title: 64 Degrees

Applied Physics and Mathematics Building.description: The Applied Physics and Mathematics building located in Muir by the Pines Dining Hall and is the home to all math and physics majors on campus. You can usually find students in office hours, attending discussions, or finishing up last minute homework in the various floors of the building.
Applied Physics and Mathematics Building.subtitle: a prison
Applied Physics and Mathematics Building.title: Applied Physics and Mathematics Building

Biomedical Library.description: The Biomedical Library has two stories, spacious, designated quiet areas, study rooms, clean restrooms, and plenty of tables and outlets! It is also a way quieter location than geisel if you are looking for a quiet place to study.
Biomedical Library.subtitle: Near Revelle
Biomedical Library.title: Biomedical Library

Canyonview Aquatic Center.description: Canyonview Aquatic Center is the main aquatic center at the University of California San Diego, comprising two Olympic-size swimming pools, bleacher seating, and associated fitness facilities. It is located on the Warren College campus and serves as the home stadium of the Triton men's and women's water polo, swimming and diving teams. It also has a weight room which features lifting equipment chosen specifically for aquatic training. The southern part of the building houses the Outback Climbing Center.
Canyonview Aquatic Center.subtitle: welcome to warren's tiny gym
Canyonview Aquatic Center.title: Canyonview Aquatic Center

Center Hall.description: Located by the end of Library walk across the steet from the medical school, Center Hall houses a variety of lectures hall that cover a plethora of majors. There is also a coffe stall outside and some stone spheres.
Center Hall.subtitle: lecture hall in the center of campus
Center Hall.title: Center Hall

Computer Science and Engineering Buildin.description: The upper floors of the CSE building mainly serve as offices for the CSE department faculty. On the other hand the subterraen floor often called the Dungeon is where you will find many sleepless cse student coding any time of the day as they try and finish their weekly PA's
Computer Science and Engineering Buildin.subtitle: smelly cs majors beware!!!!
Computer Science and Engineering Buildin.title: Computer Science and Engineering Building

Conrad Prebys Music Center.description: The Conrad Prebys Performing Arts Center is the new heart of cultural, arts education, and community event activity in La Jolla.  The Conrad is the permanent home of La Jolla Music Society and hosts world-class performances presented by LJMS as well as other San Diego arts presenters.  Additionally, The Conrad will see a wide range of conferences, corporate meetings, and private events.
Conrad Prebys Music Center.subtitle: for music
Conrad Prebys Music Center.title: Conrad Prebys Music Center

Foodworx.description: Famous for their personal pizzas, Foodworx also carries fresh salads, sandwiches, and grill specials. Soak up the sun on the patio, or get your food to-go.
Foodworx.subtitle: good sandwiches
Foodworx.title: Foodworx

Galbraith Hall.description: Formerly a campus library, Galbraith Hall was renovated and is now the center of operations for the Department of Theatre & Dance. Galbraith Hall houses faculty and graduate student offices, four large rehearsal rooms, a 99-seat theatre (Arthur Wagner Theatre) with dressing rooms and a stage management booth, and lab facilities for our undergraduate and graduate designers.
Galbraith Hall.subtitle: one of the biggest lecture halls on campus
Galbraith Hall.title: Galbraith Hall

Geisel Library.description: Geisel Library is the main library building of the University of California San Diego Library. It is named in honor of Audrey and Theodor Seuss Geisel. Theodor is better known as children's author Dr. Seuss. The building's distinctive Brutalist architecture has resulted in its being featured in the UC San Diego logo and becoming the most recognizable building on campus.
Geisel Library.subtitle: where students suffer
Geisel Library.title: Geisel Library

Goody's Place.description: Serving signature burritos and bowls all day long, Goody’s offers a variety of proteins to choose from. Whether you’re getting a breakfast burrito to-go, or fully customizing a burrito bowl and enjoying it on their spacious patio, Goody’s has you covered.
Goody's Place.subtitle: burritosssss
Goody's Place.title: Goody's Place

La Jolla Project.description: The La Jolla Project is a piece of art composed of 71 granite blocks. It was completed by Richard Fleischner in 1984 and is the third piece in the Stuart Collection. Students have nicknamed the art "Stonehenge" and commonly visit the area to study, relax, and spend time with friends.
La Jolla Project.subtitle: stonehenge
La Jolla Project.title: La Jolla Project

Library Walk.description: Library Walks is a pedestrian spine that runs through the heart of the student-services buildings and terminates at Geisel Library. The walk provides much needed structure as well as a key pedestrian link to a loosely planned and sprawling campus.
Library Walk.subtitle: spine of ucsd
Library Walk.title: Library Walk

Main Gym.description: As one of UCSD's gym facilities, the Main Gym is a popular location among students. It not only holds several basketball courts but also exercise equipment and machines. The Main Gym also hosts recreation classes, which range from aerial silks to badminton.
Main Gym.subtitle: be healthy with smaller groups of people
Main Gym.title: Main Gym

Marshall Field.description: Located near OceanView and Goody's, Marshall Field hosts a variety of sports games, not limited to soccer, flag football, ultimate frisbee, and rugby. UCSD sports teams often hold their practices here, and students are able to use the field whenever it is available.
Marshall Field.subtitle: a place to play sports with friends
Marshall Field.title: Marshall Field

Oceanview Terrace.description: This restaurant features stone hearth pizzas, salads, fresh baked desserts, Certified Kosher options, as well as, a coffee and gelato bar. It is also a frequent late night destination for students who are staying up and studying.
Oceanview Terrace.subtitle: pizzas
Oceanview Terrace.title: Oceanview Terrace

Pepper Canyon Hall.description: Pepper Canyon Hall was originally contructed as in interim building for Rady School of Management while it was under construction, and now hosts a variety of classes and offices for faculty members. It is located near the Prebsy Music Hall and Center Hall.
Pepper Canyon Hall.subtitle: one of the few lecture halls near Sixth college
Pepper Canyon Hall.title: Pepper Canyon Hall

Peterson Hall.description: eterson Hall consists of two high-capacity lecture forums as well as a few smaller classrooms. It has the Chical Legacy Mural painted across the east wall of the building.
Peterson Hall.subtitle: bio is held here and i don't like bio
Peterson Hall.title: Peterson Hall

Price Center.description: Price Center is a student center located in the center of campus, just south of Geisel Library. As one of the largest student centers in the country, Price Center serves more than 30,000 visitors a day. Price Center offers a variety of services, places, and spaces geared to the needs of students including fast food restaurants, the campus bookstore, a movie theater, and offices for various student organizations.
Price Center.subtitle: center of campus!
Price Center.title: Price Center

RIMAC.description: The Recreation, Intramural, and Athletic Complex is a sports complex comprising an arena, a weight room and various other event and athletic facilities. It is one of the largest college athletic facilities in the country. RIMAC Arena is the home arena of the UC San Diego Tritons men's and women's basketball and volleyball teams, and Triton Soccer Stadium on the adjacent RIMAC Field hosts Triton men's and women's soccer matches.
RIMAC.subtitle: be fit!
RIMAC.title: RIMAC

Rady School of Management.description: he Rady School of Management at the University of California San Diego is a graduate-level business school offering full-time and part-time Master of Business Administration programs, a full-time Master of Finance degree and a full-time Master of Science in Business Analytics degree. It also is constantly playing host to various business events.
Rady School of Management.subtitle: business sneks alert
Rady School of Management.title: Rady School of Management

Revelle Fountain.description: In 1965, Pacific Southwest Airlines donated the Revelle Fountain to UCSD. It is in the heart of Revelle at the Revelle College Plaza and is a popular spot to sit and relax between classes.
Revelle Fountain.subtitle: in Revelle
Revelle Fountain.title: Revelle Fountain

Structural and Materials Engineering Bui.description: The Structural and Materials Engineering building (SME) opened to the public on September 14, 2012. The 183,000 square foot building houses a community of artists and engineers which includes 12 visual arts studios, a gallery and performance space, and distinct visual arts research initiatives, and a state of the art paint booth. The SME building is situated on the corner of Voigt Drive and Matthews Lane near the Visual Arts Facility.
Structural and Materials Engineering Bui.subtitle: professional legos
Structural and Materials Engineering Bui.title: Structural and Materials Engineering Building

Student Services Center.description: The Student Services Center is a one-stop resource located in the heart of campus. Most student business offices are located here, so students can conveniently access multiple services in one location. The SSC also serves as the gateway to UC San Diego, with over 40,000 visitors annually passing through. Students visit the SSC with their families as prospective students, and continue to visit as they make the transition to admitted, then current UC San Diego Tritons.
Student Services Center.subtitle: resources for students
Student Services Center.title: Student Services Center

Sun God Statue.description: Sun God is a monumental statue by French-American sculptor Niki de Saint Phalle. The figurative sculpture is a 14-foot (4.3 m) multicolored bird-like creature, perched atop a 15-foot (4.6 m) tall arch-shaped, vine-covered concrete pedestal. It was Erected in February 1983 as the first of the Stuart Collection of public art projects.
Sun God Statue.subtitle: ugly bird
Sun God Statue.title: Sun God Statue

Tata Hall.description: Recently opened in February 2019, Tata Hall is the site of laboratories for those involved in classes and research related to biology and the physical sciences. With its seven floors, this building has become the hub of biological and physical science laboratories, fostering collaboration with its open layout.
Tata Hall.subtitle: named after an Indian philosopher!
Tata Hall.title: Tata Hall

The Bistro.description: A modern eatery featuring an open kitchen, sushi bar, and an exciting Pacific Rim-inspired menu. The chefs draw from various Asian cultures to serve up the freshest seafood, crisp greens, local produce inspired vegetarian fare, and noodle dishes. The ideal experience focuses on tasting a variety of flavors and sharing plates with friends.
The Bistro.subtitle: dine in food
The Bistro.title: The Bistro

The Village Market.description: The Village Market is the biggest market on campus, offering snacks and fresh produce to small kitchen appliances. Open until 1 am daily, the market is a popular place for students to get their midnight hand-crafted coffee, snack, and meal.
The Village Market.subtitle: the largest market on campus
The Village Market.title: The Village Market

Visual Arts Facilities.description: The Visual Arts Facilities building (VAF) hosts visual arts faculty and graduate student studios, a seminar room, the graduate photo lab, a computer lab, the graduate wood, metal, and machine shop, three galleries, a performance space, a sound lab and a screening room. The VAF is situated on the corner of Russell Drive and Lyman Avenue near the Gilman parking structure.
Visual Arts Facilities.subtitle: ads and spray paint
Visual Arts Facilities.title: Visual Arts Facilities

Warren Lecture Hall.description: Warren Lecture hall is located in Marshell college near the CSE building and the Jacobs School of Engineering. It has lecture halls and research facilities inside. It also conveniantly has a coffee and snack cart right in front of the building if your feeling sleepy on your way to class in the morning.
Warren Lecture Hall.subtitle: cs classes :")
Warren Lecture Hall.title: Warren Lecture Hall
